deck_name: BUDGET ELDLICH INVOKED DECK!!! UNDER 70 AUD!!!!
deck_excerpt: EASY CHEAP ELDLICH INVOKED DECK FOR UNDER 50 DOLLARS!!!!
deck_description:
Build an amazing Eldlich Invoked Deck for under 50 USD (70 AUD)!!! Built to combat all the topping meta strategies, this deck will leave your foes cowering among the terrifying Aitsu!!! While this deck can be expensive, if built correctly, you can make this deck for under 50 Dollars!!! Here are some of the cards that are a little pricey, and what you can use to replace them!!!!

Eldlich the Golden Lord: This card is usually used at 3 in meta strategies, but we found the meta strategies cower in front of The Winged Dragon of Ra! Using your amazing trap monsters to easily turbo it out!

Invocation: This is a fusion spell card that is usually ran in the topping decks, but we are using good ol polymerization!!! It works just as well at turboing out your fusions!!!

Pot of Extravagence: This deck NEEDS it's extra deck and this card is expensive so we are not running it but instead using Pot of Desires!!!!
youtube link - https://youtu.be/ANPzPsnzHy0

HERO combo deck. Goal is to use Isolde to start Needlefibre combos that end on Apollousa or Mechaba while searching you Faris and a HERO monster for its effect. This makes Vyon into a back-up starter, which can go into Isolde through either Malicious, or Sunrise. Fire Flint Lady improves this by being full combo with Stratos, while also letting you search Mask Change by searching and summoning Shadow Mist. Armageddon Knight is full combo by itself, sending Mally, then Shadow Mist after Cross-Sheep summons it. Dark Rose fairy is a free Extender during the combo, but is here to facilitate Arma Knight combos when you see your other bricks, reducing the number of hands that brick out. Extra Deck is all about turboing out your negate(s) and then using HERO and fusion spells to top off your board. Flame Swordsman into Cross Crusader bridges the gap between Cross-Sheep and Wonder Driver, which is useful for resetting Mask Change. Flame Swordsman can also be decent to end on in this deck in low-end boards, since it has a good floating effect, while having Cross Crusader gives you back-up HERO plays you can make when you are forced to Faris early.

The deck is flexible when it comes to going first or second. Going first, you can set up Zombie World and a Doomking Balerdroch. Going second, you have handtraps maindecked already like Ash Blossom and Infinite Impermanence and you can deal with backrow and negates with Twin Twister and Super Polymerization. Maindeck supplements Balerdroch Turbo. 3 Doomking Balerdroch instead of 2 as D.D. Crow and Ice Dragon's Prison exist. 3 Uni-Zombie for your main tuner plays and for sending cards to the grave. 2 Glow-Up Bloom to get large bodies like Doomking and Jack-o-Bolan out onto the field or to search lv 5 or higher zombies like Vampire Fraulein. 3 Shiranui Solitaire to summon Uni-Zombie or Glow-Up Bloom from deck. 3 Mezuki which you can choose to play at 2 who summons zombies from grave. 2 Necroworld Banshee to ensure a Zombie World on the field. 2 Vampire Fraulein for BP assurance. 3 Ash Blossom since it can trigger Doomking. And 1 Jack-o-Bolan since its boneless Ice Dragon's Prison. Spells and Traps are just ways to get grave setup. 1 One for One to summon Bloom. 3 Twin Twister for backrow and for that discard. 3 Super Polymerization to deal with your opponent's board and for a form of interruption when you set it on turn 1. 1 Foolish Burial for that grave setup. 1 Card Destruction to setup your grave and to get targets for Jack-o-Bolan and Ice Dragon's Prison. 1 Called By the Grave. 3 Zombie World which is the best floodgate. 2 Rivalry of Warlords for the Zombie World lock. 3 Infinite Impermanence for some disruption. Extra Deck isn't that important so you can choose to play Pot of Extravagance if you want. 1 Predaplant Triphyoverutum, 1 Dragonecro Nethersoul Dragon, and 1 Starving Venom Fusion Dragon for your Super Poly targets. 1 Chaos Ruler, the Chaotic Magical Dragon for the mill effect. 1 Psy-Framelord Omega for recycling banished cards and looping cards. Ironically 1 Rampaging Smashtank Rhynosaber since it's synchro Nyarla who can tag out into materials for a lv 7 synchro which would be Red-Eyes Zombie Necro Dragon which is a massive body and it has a similar monster-stealing effect to Fraulein. 1 Number 22: Zombiestein. It's a body and a negate and you can make it so yea. 1 Unchained Abomination for removal. 1 Yuki-Onna, the Absolute Zero Mayakashi which negates all banished effects and it also a potentially 2 negates per turn. Union Carrier to equip Mezuki. Crystron Halqifibrax to summon Bloom. Vampire Sucker for draw power and tribute summoning Doomking LULW. Avendread Savior for grave set-up which is sent as cost. Linkuriboh to get Bloom into the grave. Side Deck: 2 Kasha for shuffling your opponent's board into the deck. 3 Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion since it triggers Doomking. 3 Ghost Meets Girl - A Shiranui's Story to get out Solitaire. 1 Harpie's Feather Duster. 3 Lightning Storm for more removal. 3 Ice Dragon's Prison which works well with Zombie World. Draculea Vampire is bad end of story.

deck_excerpt: Non-Meta Deck That Can Put Up Negates Plus Interruptions, With Board Breakers
deck_description:
Back Ground

The Battlin Boxer Archetype was first seen in the Yu-Gi-Oh! Anime Zexal By A Barian Force Member Known as Alito. 

The debut of the Archetype was in the set Lord Of The Tachyon, and later got more support in Shadow Specters ,  Primal Origin,

and World Superstars. Hopefully Konami gives this archetype more support in future sets. 

Key Cards In The Deck/Extra Deck

  1.  Battlin Boxer Sparrer : This Card Is the best Battlin Boxer to date, it is an important extender and can be used to make Rank 4 Monsters. Sparrer has the ability to special summon it's self from hand while you control a Battlin Boxer on the field, but you can not conduct your battle phase that turn. this effect makes this the best Battlin Boxer out right now. Even though you can't go in to your battle phase when your going first you can set up a nice bored with this card.
  2. Battlin Boxer Switchitter  : While not being no where near as good as Sparrer, Switchitter Can still be very use full. Switchitter has the effect that if you have a Battlin Boxer in the graveyard you can special summon it to your side of the field. This card paired up with Foolish Burial  can get you to your best card Isolde. (More About Her Later) Those are the 2 best Battlin Boxer, now on to important extenders 
  3. Blue Mountain Butterspy : This Combo extender can help push you to make Isolde. Whit it's special summon effect from hand when you normal summon a warrior can make this the best extender if you don't open up  Sparrer. 
  4. Junk Forword : The last crucial piece of the deck is none other than Junk Forword. This card is the first card you put on the field if you open it, why you might ask? It's effect states that is you have no monsters on your field special summon this card. That's it, that's why it's the best starter. 
  5. Isolde : By far the best card in your deck. If you can make this card it's like drawing Exodia, YOU WIN. Nah, but on a real note this is the main card this card is the Heart And Soul of this deck, and it won't be a warrior deck without Isolde. This making this card Confirms that you can get Borreload Savge Dragon and Trishula The Ice Barrier Dragon.
  6. Crystron Halqifibrax : The most Annoying, Degenerate, Hated card in this current format is of course played in this deck. The Deck would not be any good without this card. It allows this deck to at least compare to some decks. Now that you know the Key Cards in this deck  it's tie for the combo. 

Combo Time

Make Isolde, (Any Way Doesn't Matter) Isolde Effect To Send 4 Equip Spells to Grave, And Special Summon Rose, Warrior Of Revenge. Next Link Isolde Into Linkross And Summon 2 Tokens. After That With Rose + 1 Token Make Accel Synchron. With Accel Synchron And linkross Create, The One The Only Halqifibrax And Special Summon Deskbot 001 From Deck/Or Hand. With Halqifibrax As Well As Deskbot 001 Make Auroradon, Then Summon 3 Tokens. Use Auroradon Effect To Pop It's Self + 1 Of It's Tokens, And Summon O-Lion.    O-Lion + Linkross Token Makes Metal Marcher, (Make Sure It Is In Extra Monster Zone) With Marcher Effect Target Accel While O-Lion Summons A Token. Then With Accel And Any Token Make Borreload Savage Dragon. (Equip Auroradon To It) With Last 3 Monsters Make Trishula Ice Barrier Dragon. 

 

Thank You For Checking Out The Deck And Change What Ever You Want With It 

 

Hope You Enjoy The Deck Profile

Rainbow Neos package in elemental heroes

Not as combo-heavy as a normal hero deck (less vulnerable to nibiru). Adds a lot of power.

Always get two heroes out on turn 1.

No Vyon/Increase engine or Destiny Hero fusion engine because those prevent you from special summoning (Rainbow Neos- not classified as a HERO and light type)

deck_description: Rank Up!

deck_excerpt:
High level dragons brought out over and over again.

9 Dragon XYZ's backed up by two Blue-Eyes ultimate dragons.

The Kaiba experience
deck_description:
IMO the strongest possible deck using fusion and the Blue-Eyes package.

<hr />

Combos:

Summon maiden with eyes of blue, activate sage with eyes of blue -> two blue eyes on the field (for an XYZ)

Dragon shrine-> mill a dragon spirit of white (counts as a normal monster so you get another discard)

-> Then mill either: white stone of legend (summon a blue-eyes in your END phase)

OR a Kidmodo dragon (skip your BATTLE phase but special summon a dragon from your hand).

<hr />

Future fusion:

Reveal "Five-headed dragon" to mill 5 different dragons (more dragons in your GY are preferred for Dragon Mirror, also lets you activate GY effects).

Dragon mirror should be used for a Blue-Eyes ultimate dragon based on situation (2 available):

-Alternative ultimate dragon: Lets you destroy 3 enemy cards if you used an alternative blue eyes as material

-Neo alternative ultimate dragon: Lets you attack 3 times with 4500 atk if this is the only card you control

<hr />

XYZ guide:

Nr 97 Draglubion can SS any of the other "number" monsters with 1 material (giving you two dragon XYZ monsters for the price of one). This is generally the best XYZ play. The best choice for each situation is:

-Nr 100: Numeron Dragon- Will have at least 9000 attack, and 8000 more if you have any XYZ dragons other than Nr 97 out. Pick this if enemy has allowed an OTK state.

-Nr 38: Hope Harbringer- Negate 1 spell/trap

-Nr 107: Galaxy-Eyes- Change all monsters to their original atk/def

-Nr C107- Tribute 2 monsters to be able to attack 3 enemy monsters (the least useful effect- 4500 atk beatstick)

The other XYZ dragons should be used situationally, eg "Hieratic Sun Dragon Overlord of Heliopolis" can be used to blow up backrow

NOTE: Thunder End Dragon can only use 2 normal dragons as material (must be Blue-Eyes white dragon)

<hr />

This deck can grind, using Deep-Eyes to remove enemy monsters and Dragon Spirit to banish spells/traps.

The overall power-level of this deck is tied to the power level of the fusion cards. If you want to take the focus away from fusion (and make this deck more competitive), cut future-fusion for imperm. This deck is not meta, but it is very consistent and fun to play.

deck_excerpt: What's a knight without a castle to protect. Stromberg provides home for the warriors and is a 1 card Isolde while protecting them for battle. Able to
deck_description: With the falling of Linkross in OCG, it brings the Infernoble ceiling low and Stromberg provides a house for them. With both Quiet Life and Stromberg, it will be hard for opponent to break our Isolde Halq board. At the same time we also searched both BLS and Immortal Phoenix Gearfried as reinforcement because you are the king and they wont fail you. The combo is simple, as it is just another Halq/Auroradon stuff. You just need Isolde, add Gearfried/BLS, ss Grappler Angler, make Halq, ss 001, make Auroradon, ss 001, make Arc Light (for early negation), use Auroradon tribute itself and 1 token, ss O-Lion, make Vanguard Roland and use its eff chain O-Lion, make Savage, add BLS at the end phase. You can even put them all at def position cus Stromberg is there to protect. Stromberg is our best card and main starter, it means Glife and Terraforming are essential. Glife is also a great toolbox as it is a s/t pop and can be summoned from deck by Stromberg. Iron Hans and Knight as our main target, run 2 each as backup cus 3 are too bricky. Renaud is there as it is a plus with Living Fossil. 2 Fire Flint Lady as our best extender and it replaces Grappler Angler if we draw that tuner (Fire Flint Lady ss Grappler from hand and both have same lv1, means u wont need more equip if summoned from Isolde). Quiet Life goes along with Stromberg as floodgate (this deck doesnt run any normal summon anyway). 3 Durendal as advantage cards (you can put another good equips too, like Axe of Fools, etc.). Staples are just there cus f*** meta, man. Extra deck is just combo pieces and generic links, play double/triple Isolde as follow up play (link climb). For side deck, Gamma is good as it kills S0 while giving us Halq or lv8 synchro. Pros: Consistent combo, multiple negations, floodgate, staples, and great followup. Cons: Stromberg banishes 10 (I tried playing 40+ cards but it makes Stromberg chance lower, but at least this deck can OTK).

deck_excerpt: This is a new altergeist deck profile for the JULY 2020 Format (BLAR and NUMERONS)
deck_description: The numerons and zexal are officially out in the TCG, which is forcing every deck to revolve around them. Zexal is not as dangerous to this deck, but it is still a threat, so this deck has many cards such as Imperm, ghost ogre and evenly matched to stop the zexal. With multifaker back at 3, altergeists actually might have a competitive chance again, and here it is. Playing tons of traps is essential for altergeists, so we have evenly matched and imperial order in the main deck. Altergeists are also another deck that can play pot of extravagance, so 3 of that as well. Imperm is obviously a must, and summon limit is in the side deck because it is so powerful. Artifact sanctum and scythe also made their way into the side deck, it is so stunning against utopic zexal and also a trap. Altergeists do a lot of summoning on the opponent's turn, so zexal isn't a massive threat but still extremely dangerous. Secret village of the spellcasters is a really good side deck card, especially against numeron. Selene is a good extender as well.

deck_excerpt: Salamangreat Control Deck for the JULY 2020 FORMAT (BLAR and Utopic Zexal)
deck_description: The numerons are now TCG legal, which is going to warp the meta by a long shot. This will be your main problem, so having as many counters to zexal as possible is a must. Ghost ogre is extremely good to get rid of the zexal so you can go into accesscode and OTK next turn (Granted you're still alive). Zexal is extremely hard to play with, so cards like ash blossom and Infinite Impermanence really help against it. You'll also want plenty of rank 4s such as bagooska and abyss dweller to stun your opponent. Traptrix rafflesia stops handtraps, especially nibiru. You could consider running artifact sanctum and scythe, which stuns most decks, but in a salamangreat deck it really isn't necessary. Cards Like parallel eXceed are good for your rank 4 plays, and also extenders. Only 2 desires are necessary, it decreases your chance of drawing more than 1 and also removes any possible chance of you drawing 2 more desires of one. In the side the the lightning storm and evenly matched can help you immensly if you're playing against zexal. You can get rid of the zexal once it has been exhausted. Summon limit and gozen match are RIDICULOUSLY good in this format, especially against things like halqifibrax and other long combos. You are technically playing 8 gazelles in this deck, so no need to worry about not drawing one. Last but now least, 2 of the salamangreat traps are really useful. You can also search them with gazelle, but they're really good to see in your hand because they are just so disruptive.

deck_name: FELGRAND DRAGON DECK,Ten Thousand Dragon 10.000 atk
deck_description: https://youtu.be/SEsvasgF14o
https://youtu.be/TlJXZFkx09o

So I've always liked Frogs. Unfortunately, Frogs do not have enough cards to make their own deck. There was a bit of hope in the Create-A-Card Project, but as you probably know, that did not go so well. So, until Frogs get more good cards, we are going to have to stick with the Paleozoics. Anyways, the focus of the Paleozoics is to slowly snowball advantage, disrupting your opponent in earlier turns and summoning them back from the GY as monsters later on in the duel. When they come back as monsters, they become level 2 aqua WATER monsters, who will be banished if they leave the field. This makes them a perfect mix with Frogs, having the right type, attribute, and level, as well as being Xyz focused, allowing them to not get banished when detached as material. One of Frog's benefits is that they can mix into practically any WATER deck. For example, if you were to open the following:
  • Swap Frog + Any WATER Monster = Coral Anemone + Toad + Dupe
    1. Pitch your WATER Monster to Special Summon Swap
    2. Swap sends Ronintoadin to the GY
    3. Bounce Swap back to your hand
    4. Normal Summon Swap
    5. Swap sends Swap/Dupe to the GY
    6. Banish Swap/Dupe from GY and Special Summon Ronin
    7. Link into Coral Anemone
    8. Use Coral Anemone's effect, Special Summon Swap
    9. Swap sends Swap/Dupe to the GY
    10. Banish Swap/Dupe from GY and Special Summon Ronin
    11. Xyz Summon Toadally Awesome
    12. During the Opponent's Standby Phase, activate Toad's effect and Special Summon Dupe
One big flaw with Frogs is that they are weak. Their stats are too low to be taken as a threat, hence why they prefer going first, preventing your opponent from building their board. Dupe provides a solution for that. If you have 2 Dupe Frogs out, they will prevent your opponent from attacking altogether. Notice in the combo above, we never used Swap's final effect, which gives you an additional Normal Summon, as long as it is used for a Frog. If you open Swap + Dupe + Any WATER Monster, you will be able to end on Coral Anemone + Toad + 2 Dupes. On an additional note, since the main deck does not have any WATER Monsters other than Frogs, we will always have an extra mill in the above combo. This means we can send an extra Ronin to the GY. Nibiru is a popular hand trap right now. But, just because a hand trap is good, doesn't mean everyone knows how to make the most of it. If your opponent plays Nibiru the moment you hit 5 summons, it would be at Step 9, right after you milled for the final time with Swap. Adjust the combo so that you have 2 Ronins and 1 Frog (Swap/Dupe). If your opponent plays Nibiru right there and then, you would 2 Frogs and 2 Ronins in the GY (and a Coral Anemone, but that doesn't matter here). Banish the 2 Frogs, Special Summon both Ronins, and overlay for a Toad. Note that if your opponent is smart, they would wait for Step 10, and then they would play the Nibiru. Nothing you can do about that. As for Scapegoat:
  1. Set Scapegoat during your turn. To get around the restriction, you need to play it during your opponent's turn, preferably during the End Phase.
  2. During your turn, use 2 of the tokens to summon I:P Masquerena
  3. Use the other tokens to summon Linkuriboh and Link Spider
  4. Use all 3 of the link monsters to summon either Borrelsword or Borreload (note that they will have I:P's protection)
All suggestions are welcome and appreciated.

deck_excerpt: Stun your opponent with Zexal, Handtraps and Floodgates and summon the mighty Rainbow Neos.
deck_description: Stun your opponent with Zexal, Handtraps and Floodgates and summon the mighty Rainbow Neos.   The best way to summon Rainbow Neos is through the Predaplant enginge (Scorpio to SS Cobra to search Neos Fusion). That way before you activate Neos Fusion (since Neos Fusion locks you out of SS for the remainder of the turn) you can either link them into Beat Cop from the Underworld to give Neos extra protection, overlay them into The Phantom Knights of Break Sword to destroy an opponents card (only useful if going second) or overlay them into Number 3: Cicada King for disruption. Obviously none of that compares to playing the Numeron engine Turn 1 and then crushing your opponent from there.   The Predaplant engine can also be used to search Instant Fusion to SS Thousand-Eyes Restrict to link all 3 into Selene, Queen of the Master Magicians. If there are 3 spells in the GYs or field you can then SS Thousand-Eyes Restrict from GY, link Restrict into Linkuriboh and link Selene and Linkuriboh into Accesscode Talker (or any other Link-4 that works). If you used the Numeron engine prior on your last turn you will have enough Spells for Selene's effect (Instant Fusion and Numeron Calling in GY and Numeron Network on field).   Since Neos doesn't provide much interaction with your opponent the handtraps and floodgates will come in handy since There Can Be Only One doesn't stop you from summoning Rainbow Neos (it does prevent you from summoning more than 1 Numeron Gate and from using the Predaplant engine so keep that in mind).

deck_excerpt: only aggro Paleofrog deck to exist with a scrap engine for a one card Trishula combo
deck_description: Simultaneously big/ape brain paleofrogs with a scrap engine. Play recycler with another card in your hand for a single card combo to summon trishula. Summon recycler and send o-lion to the graveyard for the token so you can link into wyvern, use it to get out scrap golem, and use its ability to summon recycler again and send jet synchron to the graveyard. Then discard your other card to summon it and you can synchro. Alternatively if you have a level 2 monster on the field and scrap worm or golem in your graveyard already you can use recycler to get wyvern and get out scrap golem, and use it to summon the worm and synchro trishula. Sometimes you banish jet synchron, golem, or worm with pot of desires so your fallback is borrelsword and samurai destroyer or black rose dragon; real talk on a related note leanchoilia is underrated and makes it possible to win when you'd otherwise be sol, not to mention you can use it to recycle back jack and frogs for ronin summons. Get out the scum toad asap as per usual, usually you can get out opabinia and use it's ability to get another paleo on the field to summon toad, or don't. This deck has engines like an illegally modified honda civic, so you have options even if you face a set back. Just don't jump the gun with your negates or it's hut. Sometimes summoning trishula is not optimal, it's more like the icing on the cake, sometimes it's fantastic by itself but usually it's better when there's a cake already you feel me. Shrub serpent, solemn no card, and back jack package are for dealing with lightning storm and the like. if you have two shrub serpents out that get destroyed, I highly recommend you summon samurai destroyer and dupe frog, trust me on this one. My preference would be for witch's strike over shrub serpent or solemn judgement for sheer maximization of cheekiness and to punish everyone for using hand traps, but unfortunately it's bugged in ygo pro. Eria is in the side deck for when you have to deal with needlefiber or mermails. Extra deck space is tight what with all your toolbox responses, so the only knightmare is the unicorn because i had to cut compulsory evacuation device to make space for cards that don't target, since your biggest hang ups will be monsters with built in protection. It's also why quaking mirror force and evenly matched are in the side deck. Wind up snail is also in the side deck because it returns a set card to the hand, but also you can send it to the graveyard to special summon swap frog. Last but not least, if you draw both a frog and a recycler, hold onto one and use the other to bait out negations and such for smoother sailing turn two. You can throw your opponent for a lot of loops they wouldn't expect from your average paleofrog deck. If I could just play scraps and have a good time I wouldn't have had to work so hard on this.

deck_description: This deck is the first in a progressive series wherein we're opening 24 of every pack in chronological release order. 50 cards in Main deck.
